22 // Liftoff Frames.
23 //
24 // slot Frame
25 // +--------------------+---------------------------
26 // n+4 | optional padding slot to keep the stack 16 byte aligned.
27 // n+3 | parameter n |
28 // ... | ... |
29 // 4 | parameter 1 | or parameter 2
30 // 3 | parameter 0 | or parameter 1
31 // 2 | (result address) | or parameter 0
32 // -----+--------------------+---------------------------
33 // 1 | return addr (lr) |
34 // 0 | previous frame (fp)|
35 // -----+--------------------+ <-- frame ptr (fp)
36 // -1 | StackFrame::WASM |
37 // -2 | instance |
38 // -3 | feedback vector|
39 // -----+--------------------+---------------------------
40 // -4 | slot 0 | ^
41 // -5 | slot 1 | |
42 // | | Frame slots
43 // | | |
44 // | | v
45 // | optional padding slot to keep the stack 16 byte aligned.
46 // -----+--------------------+ <-- stack ptr (sp)
47 //
48 
49 inline MemOperand GetStackSlot(int offset) { return MemOperand(fp, -offset); }
50 
51 inline MemOperand GetInstanceDataOperand() {
52  return GetStackSlot(WasmLiftoffFrameConstants::kInstanceDataOffset);
53 }
54 
55 inline CPURegister GetRegFromType(const LiftoffRegister& reg, ValueKind kind) {
56  switch (kind) {
57  case kI32:
58  return reg.gp().W();
59  case kI64:
60  case kRef:
61  case kRefNull:
62  return reg.gp().X();
63  case kF32:
64  return reg.fp().S();
65  case kF64:
66  return reg.fp().D();
67  case kS128:
68  return reg.fp().Q();
69  default:
70  UNREACHABLE();
71  }
72 }
73 
74 inline CPURegList PadRegList(RegList list) {
75  if ((list.Count() & 1) != 0) list.set(padreg);
76  return CPURegList(kXRegSizeInBits, list);
77 }
78 
79 inline CPURegList PadVRegList(DoubleRegList list) {
80  if ((list.Count() & 1) != 0) list.set(fp_scratch);
81  return CPURegList(kQRegSizeInBits, list);
82 }
83 
84 inline CPURegister AcquireByType(UseScratchRegisterScope* temps,
85  ValueKind kind) {
86  switch (kind) {
87  case kI32:
88  return temps->AcquireW();
89  case kI64:
90  case kRef:
91  case kRefNull:
92  return temps->AcquireX();
93  case kF32:
94  return temps->AcquireS();
95  case kF64:
96  return temps->AcquireD();
97  case kS128:
98  return temps->AcquireQ();
99  default:
100  UNREACHABLE();
101  }
102 }

104 template <typename T>
105 inline MemOperand GetMemOp(LiftoffAssembler* assm,
106  UseScratchRegisterScope* temps, Register addr,
107  Register offset, T offset_imm,
108  bool i64_offset = false, unsigned shift_amount = 0) {
109  if (!offset.is_valid()) return MemOperand(addr.X(), offset_imm);
110  Register effective_addr = addr.X();
111  if (offset_imm) {
112  effective_addr = temps->AcquireX();
113  assm->Add(effective_addr, addr.X(), offset_imm);
114  }
115  return i64_offset
116  ? MemOperand(effective_addr, offset.X(), LSL, shift_amount)
117  : MemOperand(effective_addr, offset.W(), UXTW, shift_amount);
118 }
119 
120 // Compute the effective address (sum of |addr|, |offset| (if given) and
121 // |offset_imm|) into a temporary register. This is needed for certain load
122 // instructions that do not support an offset (register or immediate).
123 // Returns |addr| if both |offset| and |offset_imm| are zero.
124 inline Register GetEffectiveAddress(LiftoffAssembler* assm,
125  UseScratchRegisterScope* temps,
126  Register addr, Register offset,
127  uintptr_t offset_imm,
128  bool i64_offset = false) {
129  if (!offset.is_valid() && offset_imm == 0) return addr;
130  Register tmp = temps->AcquireX();
131  if (offset.is_valid()) {
132  assm->Add(tmp, addr, i64_offset ? Operand(offset) : Operand(offset, UXTW));
133  addr = tmp;
134  }
135  if (offset_imm != 0) assm->Add(tmp, addr, offset_imm);
136  return tmp;
137 }
138 
139 enum class ShiftDirection : bool { kLeft, kRight };
140 
141 enum class ShiftSign : bool { kSigned, kUnsigned };
142 
143 template <ShiftDirection dir, ShiftSign sign = ShiftSign::kSigned>
144 inline void EmitSimdShift(LiftoffAssembler* assm, VRegister dst, VRegister lhs,
145  Register rhs, VectorFormat format) {
146  DCHECK_IMPLIES(dir == ShiftDirection::kLeft, sign == ShiftSign::kSigned);
147  DCHECK(dst.IsSameFormat(lhs));
148  DCHECK_EQ(dst.LaneCount(), LaneCountFromFormat(format));
149 
150  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(assm);
151  VRegister tmp = temps.AcquireV(format);
152  Register shift = dst.Is2D() ? temps.AcquireX() : temps.AcquireW();
153  int mask = LaneSizeInBitsFromFormat(format) - 1;
154  assm->And(shift, rhs, mask);
155  assm->Dup(tmp, shift);
156 
157  if (dir == ShiftDirection::kRight) {
158  assm->Neg(tmp, tmp);
159  }
160 
161  if (sign == ShiftSign::kSigned) {
162  assm->Sshl(dst, lhs, tmp);
163  } else {
164  assm->Ushl(dst, lhs, tmp);
165  }
166 }
167 
168 template <VectorFormat format, ShiftSign sign>
169 inline void EmitSimdShiftRightImmediate(LiftoffAssembler* assm, VRegister dst,
170  VRegister lhs, int32_t rhs) {
171  // Sshr and Ushr does not allow shifts to be 0, so check for that here.
172  int mask = LaneSizeInBitsFromFormat(format) - 1;
173  int32_t shift = rhs & mask;
174  if (!shift) {
175  if (dst != lhs) {
176  assm->Mov(dst, lhs);
177  }
178  return;
179  }
180 
181  if (sign == ShiftSign::kSigned) {
182  assm->Sshr(dst, lhs, rhs & mask);
183  } else {
184  assm->Ushr(dst, lhs, rhs & mask);
185  }
186 }
187 
188 inline void EmitAnyTrue(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
189  LiftoffRegister src) {
190  // AnyTrue does not depend on the number of lanes, so we can use V4S for all.
191  UseScratchRegisterScope scope(assm);
192  VRegister temp = scope.AcquireV(kFormat4S);
193  assm->Umaxp(temp, src.fp().V4S(), src.fp().V4S());
194  assm->Fmov(dst.gp().X(), temp.D());
195  assm->Cmp(dst.gp().X(), 0);
196  assm->Cset(dst.gp().W(), ne);
197 }
198 
199 inline void EmitAllTrue(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst,
200  LiftoffRegister src, VectorFormat format) {
201  UseScratchRegisterScope scope(assm);
202  VRegister temp = scope.AcquireV(ScalarFormatFromFormat(format));
203  assm->Uminv(temp, VRegister::Create(src.fp().code(), format));
204  assm->Umov(dst.gp().W(), temp, 0);
205  assm->Cmp(dst.gp().W(), 0);
206  assm->Cset(dst.gp().W(), ne);
207 }
208 
209 inline CPURegister LoadToRegister(LiftoffAssembler* assm,
210  UseScratchRegisterScope* temps,
211  const LiftoffAssembler::VarState& src) {
212  if (src.is_reg()) {
213  return GetRegFromType(src.reg(), src.kind());
214  }
215  if (src.is_const()) {
216  if (src.kind() == kI32) {
217  if (src.i32_const() == 0) return wzr;
218  Register temp = temps->AcquireW();
219  assm->Mov(temp, src.i32_const());
220  return temp;
221  }
222  DCHECK_EQ(kI64, src.kind());
223  if (src.i32_const() == 0) return xzr;
224  Register temp = temps->AcquireX();
225  assm->Mov(temp, static_cast<int64_t>(src.i32_const()));
226  return temp;
227  }
228  DCHECK(src.is_stack());
229  CPURegister temp = AcquireByType(temps, src.kind());
230  assm->Ldr(temp, GetStackSlot(src.offset()));
231  return temp;
232 }
233 
234 inline void StoreToMemory(LiftoffAssembler* assm, MemOperand dst,
235  const LiftoffAssembler::VarState& src) {
236  if (src.kind() == kI16) {
237  DCHECK(src.is_reg());
238  assm->Strh(src.reg().gp(), dst);
239  return;
240  }
241  UseScratchRegisterScope temps{assm};
242  CPURegister src_reg = LoadToRegister(assm, &temps, src);
243  assm->Str(src_reg, dst);
244 }

248 int LiftoffAssembler::PrepareStackFrame() {
249  int offset = pc_offset();
250  InstructionAccurateScope scope(this, 1);
251  // Next we reserve the memory for the whole stack frame. We do not know yet
252  // how big the stack frame will be so we just emit a placeholder instruction.
253  // PatchPrepareStackFrame will patch this in order to increase the stack
254  // appropriately.
255  sub(sp, sp, 0);
256  return offset;
257 }
258 
259 void LiftoffAssembler::CallFrameSetupStub(int declared_function_index) {
260 // The standard library used by gcc tryjobs does not consider `std::find` to be
261 // `constexpr`, so wrap it in a `#ifdef __clang__` block.
262 #ifdef __clang__
263  static_assert(std::find(std::begin(wasm::kGpParamRegisters),
264  std::end(wasm::kGpParamRegisters),
265  kLiftoffFrameSetupFunctionReg) ==
266  std::end(wasm::kGpParamRegisters));
267 #endif
268 
269  // On ARM64, we must push at least {lr} before calling the stub, otherwise
270  // it would get clobbered with no possibility to recover it. So just set
271  // up the frame here.
272  EnterFrame(StackFrame::WASM);
273  LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister(kLiftoffFrameSetupFunctionReg),
274  WasmValue(declared_function_index));
275  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmLiftoffFrameSetup);
276 }
277 
278 void LiftoffAssembler::PrepareTailCall(int num_callee_stack_params,
279  int stack_param_delta) {
280  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
281  temps.Exclude(x16, x17);
282 
283  // This is the previous stack pointer value (before we push the lr and the
284  // fp). We need to keep it to autenticate the lr and adjust the new stack
285  // pointer afterwards.
286  Add(x16, fp, 16);
287 
288  // Load the fp and lr of the old frame, they will be pushed in the new frame
289  // during the actual call.
290 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CONTROL_FLOW_INTEGRITY
291  Ldp(fp, x17, MemOperand(fp));
292  Autib1716();
293  Mov(lr, x17);
294 #else
295  Ldp(fp, lr, MemOperand(fp));
296 #endif
297 
298  temps.Include(x17);
299 
300  Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
301 
302  // Shift the whole frame upwards, except for fp and lr.
303  // Adjust x16 to be the new stack pointer first, so that {str} doesn't need
304  // a temp register to materialize the offset.
305  Sub(x16, x16, stack_param_delta * 8);
306  int slot_count = num_callee_stack_params;
307  for (int i = slot_count - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
308  ldr(scratch, MemOperand(sp, i * 8));
309  str(scratch, MemOperand(x16, i * 8));
310  }
311 
312  // Set the new stack pointer.
313  mov(sp, x16);
314 }
315 
316 void LiftoffAssembler::AlignFrameSize() {
317  // The frame_size includes the frame marker. The frame marker has already been
318  // pushed on the stack though, so we don't need to allocate memory for it
319  // anymore.
320  int frame_size = GetTotalFrameSize() - 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
321 
322  static_assert(kStackSlotSize == kXRegSize,
323  "kStackSlotSize must equal kXRegSize");
324 
325  // The stack pointer is required to be quadword aligned.
326  // Misalignment will cause a stack alignment fault.
327  int misalignment = frame_size % kQuadWordSizeInBytes;
328  if (misalignment) {
329  int padding = kQuadWordSizeInBytes - misalignment;
330  frame_size += padding;
331  max_used_spill_offset_ += padding;
332  }
333 }
334 
335 void LiftoffAssembler::PatchPrepareStackFrame(
336  int offset, SafepointTableBuilder* safepoint_table_builder,
337  bool feedback_vector_slot, size_t stack_param_slots) {
338  // The frame_size includes the frame marker and the instance slot. Both are
339  // pushed as part of frame construction, so we don't need to allocate memory
340  // for them anymore.
341  int frame_size = GetTotalFrameSize() - 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
342  // The frame setup builtin also pushes the feedback vector, and an unused
343  // slot for alignment.
344  if (feedback_vector_slot) {
345  frame_size = std::max(frame_size - 2 * kSystemPointerSize, 0);
346  }
347 
348  // The stack pointer is required to be quadword aligned.
349  // Misalignment will cause a stack alignment fault.
350  DCHECK_EQ(frame_size, RoundUp(frame_size, kQuadWordSizeInBytes));
351 
352  PatchingAssembler patching_assembler(zone(), AssemblerOptions{},
353  buffer_start_ + offset, 1);
354 
355  if (V8_LIKELY(frame_size < 4 * KB)) {
356  // This is the standard case for small frames: just subtract from SP and be
357  // done with it.
358  DCHECK(IsImmAddSub(frame_size));
359  patching_assembler.PatchSubSp(frame_size);
360  return;
361  }
362 
363  // The frame size is bigger than 4KB, so we might overflow the available stack
364  // space if we first allocate the frame and then do the stack check (we will
365  // need some remaining stack space for throwing the exception). That's why we
366  // check the available stack space before we allocate the frame. To do this we
367  // replace the {__ sub(sp, sp, framesize)} with a jump to OOL code that does
368  // this "extended stack check".
369  //
370  // The OOL code can simply be generated here with the normal assembler,
371  // because all other code generation, including OOL code, has already finished
372  // when {PatchPrepareStackFrame} is called. The function prologue then jumps
373  // to the current {pc_offset()} to execute the OOL code for allocating the
374  // large frame.
375 
376  // Emit the unconditional branch in the function prologue (from {offset} to
377  // {pc_offset()}).
378  patching_assembler.b((pc_offset() - offset) >> kInstrSizeLog2);
379 
380  // If the frame is bigger than the stack, we throw the stack overflow
381  // exception unconditionally. Thereby we can avoid the integer overflow
382  // check in the condition code.
383  RecordComment("OOL: stack check for large frame");
384  Label continuation;
385  if (frame_size < v8_flags.stack_size * 1024) {
386  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
387  Register stack_limit = temps.AcquireX();
388  LoadStackLimit(stack_limit, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
389  Add(stack_limit, stack_limit, Operand(frame_size));
390  Cmp(sp, stack_limit);
391  B(hs /* higher or same */, &continuation);
392  }
393 
394  if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
395  LiftoffRegList regs_to_save;
396  regs_to_save.set(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::GapRegister());
397  regs_to_save.set(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister());
398  for (auto reg : kGpParamRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
399  for (auto reg : kFpParamRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
400  PushRegisters(regs_to_save);
401  Mov(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::GapRegister(), frame_size);
402  Add(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister(), fp,
403  Operand(stack_param_slots * kSystemPointerSize +
404  CommonFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp));
405  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmHandleStackOverflow);
406  safepoint_table_builder->DefineSafepoint(this);
407  PopRegisters(regs_to_save);
408  } else {
409  Call(static_cast<Address>(Builtin::kWasmStackOverflow),
410  RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
411  // The call will not return; just define an empty safepoint.
412  safepoint_table_builder->DefineSafepoint(this);
413  if (v8_flags.debug_code) Brk(0);
414  }
415 
416  bind(&continuation);
417 
418  // Now allocate the stack space. Note that this might do more than just
419  // decrementing the SP; consult {MacroAssembler::Claim}.
420  Claim(frame_size, 1);
421 
422  // Jump back to the start of the function, from {pc_offset()} to
423  // right after the reserved space for the {__ sub(sp, sp, framesize)} (which
424  // is a branch now).
425  int func_start_offset = offset + kInstrSize;
426  b((func_start_offset - pc_offset()) >> kInstrSizeLog2);
427 }

453 void LiftoffAssembler::CheckTierUp(int declared_func_index, int budget_used,
454  Label* ool_label,
455  const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
456  UseScratchRegisterScope temps{this};
457  Register budget_array = temps.AcquireX();
458 
459  Register instance_data = cache_state_.cached_instance_data;
460  if (instance_data == no_reg) {
461  instance_data = budget_array; // Reuse the temp register.
462  LoadInstanceDataFromFrame(instance_data);
463  }
464 
465  constexpr int kArrayOffset = wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
466  WasmTrustedInstanceData::kTieringBudgetArrayOffset);
467  ldr(budget_array, MemOperand{instance_data, kArrayOffset});
468 
469  int budget_arr_offset = kInt32Size * declared_func_index;
470  // If the offset cannot be used in the operand directly, add it once to the
471  // budget_array to avoid doing that two times below.
472  if (!IsImmLSScaled(budget_arr_offset, 2 /* log2(sizeof(i32)) */) &&
473  !IsImmLSUnscaled(budget_arr_offset)) {
474  Add(budget_array, budget_array, budget_arr_offset);
475  budget_arr_offset = 0;
476  }
477 
478  Register budget = temps.AcquireW();
479  MemOperand budget_addr{budget_array, budget_arr_offset};
480  ldr(budget, budget_addr);
481  // Make sure that the {budget_used} can be used as an immediate for SUB.
482  if (budget_used > 0xFFF000) {
483  budget_used = 0xFFF000; // 16'773'120
484  } else if (budget_used > 0xFFF) {
485  budget_used &= 0xFFF000;
486  }
487  DCHECK(IsImmAddSub(budget_used));
488  AddSub(budget, budget, Operand{budget_used}, SetFlags, SUB);
489  str(budget, budget_addr);
490  B(ool_label, mi);
491 }
492 
493 Register LiftoffAssembler::LoadOldFramePointer() {
494  if (!v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
495  return fp;
496  }
497  LiftoffRegister old_fp = GetUnusedRegister(RegClass::kGpReg, {});
498  Label done, call_runtime;
499  Ldr(old_fp.gp(), MemOperand(fp, TypedFrameConstants::kFrameTypeOffset));
500  Cmp(old_fp.gp(),
501  Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START)));
502  B(eq, &call_runtime);
503  Mov(old_fp.gp(), fp);
504  jmp(&done);
505 
506  bind(&call_runtime);
507  LiftoffRegList regs_to_save = cache_state()->used_registers;
508  PushRegisters(regs_to_save);
509  Mov(kCArgRegs[0], ExternalReference::isolate_address());
510  CallCFunction(ExternalReference::wasm_load_old_fp(), 1);
511  if (old_fp.gp() != kReturnRegister0) {
512  Mov(old_fp.gp(), kReturnRegister0);
513  }
514  PopRegisters(regs_to_save);
515 
516  bind(&done);
517  return old_fp.gp();
518 }
519 
520 void LiftoffAssembler::CheckStackShrink() {
521  {
522  UseScratchRegisterScope temps{this};
523  Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
524  Ldr(scratch, MemOperand(fp, TypedFrameConstants::kFrameTypeOffset));
525  Cmp(scratch,
526  Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START)));
527  }
528  Label done;
529  B(ne, &done);
530  LiftoffRegList regs_to_save;
531  for (auto reg : kGpReturnRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
532  for (auto reg : kFpReturnRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
533  PushRegisters(regs_to_save);
534  Mov(kCArgRegs[0], ExternalReference::isolate_address());
535  CallCFunction(ExternalReference::wasm_shrink_stack(), 1);
536  Mov(fp, kReturnRegister0);
537  PopRegisters(regs_to_save);
538  if (options().enable_simulator_code) {
539  // The next instruction after shrinking stack is leaving the frame.
540  // So SP will be set to old FP there. Switch simulator stack limit here.
541  UseScratchRegisterScope temps{this};
542  temps.Exclude(x16);
543  LoadStackLimit(x16, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
544  hlt(kImmExceptionIsSwitchStackLimit);
545  }
546  bind(&done);
547 }

549 void LiftoffAssembler::LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister reg, WasmValue value) {
550  switch (value.type().kind()) {
551  case kI32:
552  Mov(reg.gp().W(), value.to_i32());
553  break;
554  case kI64:
555  Mov(reg.gp().X(), value.to_i64());
556  break;
557  case kF32:
558  Fmov(reg.fp().S(), value.to_f32());
559  break;
560  case kF64:
561  Fmov(reg.fp().D(), value.to_f64());
562  break;
563  default:
564  UNREACHABLE();
565  }
566 }

578 void LiftoffAssembler::LoadFromInstance(Register dst, Register instance,
579  int offset, int size) {
580  DCHECK_LE(0, offset);
581  MemOperand src{instance, offset};
582  switch (size) {
583  case 1:
584  Ldrb(dst.W(), src);
585  break;
586  case 4:
587  Ldr(dst.W(), src);
588  break;
589  case 8:
590  Ldr(dst, src);
591  break;
592  default:
593  UNIMPLEMENTED();
594  }
595 }

597 void LiftoffAssembler::LoadTaggedPointerFromInstance(Register dst,
598  Register instance,
599  int offset) {
600  DCHECK_LE(0, offset);
601  LoadTaggedField(dst, MemOperand{instance, offset});

608 void LiftoffAssembler::ResetOSRTarget() {}

610 enum class LoadOrStore : bool { kLoad, kStore };
611 
612 // The purpose of this class is to reconstruct the PC offset of a protected
613 // instruction (load or store) that has just been emitted. We cannot simply
614 // record the current PC offset before emitting the instruction, because the
615 // respective helper function we call might emit more than one instruction
616 // (e.g. to load an immediate into a register, or to get a constant pool
617 // out of the way).
618 //
619 // Template arguments:
620 // kLoadOrStore:
621 // DCHECK that the detected protected instruction has the right type.
622 // kExtraEmittedInstructions:
623 // By default, we assume that when the destructor runs, the PC is right
624 // behind the protected instruction. If additional instructions are expected
625 // to have been emitted (such as a pointer decompression), specify their
626 // number here.
627 template <LoadOrStore kLoadOrStore, uint8_t kExtraEmittedInstructions = 0>
628 class GetProtectedInstruction {
629  public:
630  GetProtectedInstruction(LiftoffAssembler* assm,
631  uint32_t* protected_instruction_pc)
632  : assm_(assm),
633  protected_instruction_pc_(protected_instruction_pc),
634  // First emit any required pools...
635  blocked_pools_scope_(assm, kReservedInstructions * kInstrSize),
636  // ...then record the PC offset before the relevant instruction
637  // sequence.
638  previous_pc_offset_(assm->pc_offset()) {}
639 
640  ~GetProtectedInstruction() {
641  if (!protected_instruction_pc_) return;
642  *protected_instruction_pc_ =
643  assm_->pc_offset() - kInstrSize * (1 + kExtraEmittedInstructions);
644  if constexpr (kLoadOrStore == LoadOrStore::kLoad) {
645  DCHECK(assm_->InstructionAt(*protected_instruction_pc_)->IsLoad());
646  } else {
647  DCHECK(assm_->InstructionAt(*protected_instruction_pc_)->IsStore());
648  }
649  // Make sure {kReservedInstructions} was large enough.
650  DCHECK_LE(assm_->pc_offset() - previous_pc_offset_,
651  kReservedInstructions * kInstrSize);
652  USE(previous_pc_offset_);
653  }
654 
655  private:
656  // For simplicity, we hard-code this value. We could make it a template
657  // argument if we needed more flexibility. It must be at least the maximum
658  // length of the instruction sequence emitted by the {LoadTaggedField} etc.
659  // helper functions below.
660  static constexpr int kReservedInstructions = 4;
661 
662  LiftoffAssembler* assm_;
663  uint32_t* protected_instruction_pc_;
664  MacroAssembler::BlockPoolsScope blocked_pools_scope_;
665  int previous_pc_offset_;
666 };
667 
668 void LiftoffAssembler::LoadTaggedPointer(Register dst, Register src_addr,
669  Register offset_reg,
670  int32_t offset_imm,
671  uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
672  bool needs_shift) {
673  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
674  unsigned shift_amount = !needs_shift ? 0 : COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL ? 2 : 3;
675  MemOperand src_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(this, &temps, src_addr, offset_reg,
676  offset_imm, false, shift_amount);
677  DCHECK(!src_op.IsPostIndex()); // See MacroAssembler::LoadStoreMacroComplex.
678  constexpr uint8_t kDecompressionInstruction = COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL ? 1 : 0;
679  GetProtectedInstruction<LoadOrStore::kLoad, kDecompressionInstruction>
680  collect_protected_load(this, protected_load_pc);
681  LoadTaggedField(dst, src_op);
682 }

709 void LiftoffAssembler::StoreTaggedPointer(Register dst_addr,
710  Register offset_reg,
711  int32_t offset_imm, Register src,
712  LiftoffRegList /* pinned */,
713  uint32_t* protected_store_pc,
714  SkipWriteBarrier skip_write_barrier) {
715  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
716  Operand offset_op = offset_reg.is_valid() ? Operand(offset_reg.W(), UXTW)
717  : Operand(offset_imm);
718  // This is similar to {liftoff::GetMemOp}, but leaves {dst_addr} alone, and
719  // gives us a combined {offset_op}, which we need for the write barrier
720  // below. The 32-bit addition is okay because on-heap offsets don't get
721  // bigger than that.
722  if (offset_reg.is_valid() && offset_imm) {
723  Register effective_offset = temps.AcquireX();
724  Add(effective_offset.W(), offset_reg.W(), offset_imm);
725  offset_op = effective_offset;
726  }
727  {
728  GetProtectedInstruction<LoadOrStore::kStore> collect_protected_store(
729  this, protected_store_pc);
730  StoreTaggedField(src, MemOperand(dst_addr.X(), offset_op));
731  }
732 
733  if (skip_write_barrier || v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) return;
734 
735  // The write barrier.
736  Label exit;
737  CheckPageFlag(dst_addr, MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask,
738  kZero, &exit);
739  JumpIfSmi(src, &exit);
740  CheckPageFlag(src, MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask, eq, &exit);
741  CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(dst_addr, offset_op, SaveFPRegsMode::kSave,
742  StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
743  bind(&exit);
744 }

746 void LiftoffAssembler::Load(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
747  Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
748  LoadType type, uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
749  bool /* is_load_mem */, bool i64_offset,
750  bool needs_shift) {
751  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
752  unsigned shift_amount = needs_shift ? type.size_log_2() : 0;
753  MemOperand src_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(this, &temps, src_addr, offset_reg,
754  offset_imm, i64_offset, shift_amount);
755  DCHECK(!src_op.IsPostIndex()); // See MacroAssembler::LoadStoreMacroComplex.
756  GetProtectedInstruction<LoadOrStore::kLoad> collect_protected_load(
757  this, protected_load_pc);
758  switch (type.value()) {
759  case LoadType::kI32Load8U:
760  case LoadType::kI64Load8U:
761  Ldrb(dst.gp().W(), src_op);
762  break;
763  case LoadType::kI32Load8S:
764  Ldrsb(dst.gp().W(), src_op);
765  break;
766  case LoadType::kI64Load8S:
767  Ldrsb(dst.gp().X(), src_op);
768  break;
769  case LoadType::kI32Load16U:
770  case LoadType::kI64Load16U:
771  Ldrh(dst.gp().W(), src_op);
772  break;
773  case LoadType::kI32Load16S:
774  Ldrsh(dst.gp().W(), src_op);
775  break;
776  case LoadType::kI64Load16S:
777  Ldrsh(dst.gp().X(), src_op);
778  break;
779  case LoadType::kI32Load:
780  case LoadType::kI64Load32U:
781  Ldr(dst.gp().W(), src_op);
782  break;
783  case LoadType::kI64Load32S:
784  Ldrsw(dst.gp().X(), src_op);
785  break;
786  case LoadType::kI64Load:
787  Ldr(dst.gp().X(), src_op);
788  break;
789  case LoadType::kF32Load:
790  Ldr(dst.fp().S(), src_op);
791  break;
792  case LoadType::kF32LoadF16: {
793  CpuFeatureScope scope(this, FP16);
794  Ldr(dst.fp().H(), src_op);
795  Fcvt(dst.fp().S(), dst.fp().H());
796  break;
797  }
798  case LoadType::kF64Load:
799  Ldr(dst.fp().D(), src_op);
800  break;
801  case LoadType::kS128Load:
802  Ldr(dst.fp().Q(), src_op);
803  break;
804  }
805 }

807 void LiftoffAssembler::Store(Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
808  uintptr_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
809  StoreType type, LiftoffRegList /* pinned */,
810  uint32_t* protected_store_pc,
811  bool /* is_store_mem */, bool i64_offset) {
812  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
813  MemOperand dst_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(this, &temps, dst_addr, offset_reg,
814  offset_imm, i64_offset);
815  DCHECK(!dst_op.IsPostIndex()); // See MacroAssembler::LoadStoreMacroComplex.
816  GetProtectedInstruction<LoadOrStore::kStore> collect_protected_store(
817  this, protected_store_pc);
818  switch (type.value()) {
819  case StoreType::kI32Store8:
820  case StoreType::kI64Store8:
821  Strb(src.gp().W(), dst_op);
822  break;
823  case StoreType::kI32Store16:
824  case StoreType::kI64Store16:
825  Strh(src.gp().W(), dst_op);
826  break;
827  case StoreType::kI32Store:
828  case StoreType::kI64Store32:
829  Str(src.gp().W(), dst_op);
830  break;
831  case StoreType::kI64Store:
832  Str(src.gp().X(), dst_op);
833  break;
834  case StoreType::kF32StoreF16: {
835  CpuFeatureScope scope(this, FP16);
836  Fcvt(src.fp().H(), src.fp().S());
837  Str(src.fp().H(), dst_op);
838  break;
839  }
840  case StoreType::kF32Store:
841  Str(src.fp().S(), dst_op);
842  break;
843  case StoreType::kF64Store:
844  Str(src.fp().D(), dst_op);
845  break;
846  case StoreType::kS128Store:
847  Str(src.fp().Q(), dst_op);
848  break;
849  }
850 }

852 namespace liftoff {
853 #define __ lasm->
854 
855 inline Register CalculateActualAddress(LiftoffAssembler* lasm,
856  UseScratchRegisterScope& temps,
857  Register addr_reg, Register offset_reg,
858  uintptr_t offset_imm) {
859  DCHECK_NE(addr_reg, no_reg);
860  if (offset_reg == no_reg && offset_imm == 0) return addr_reg;
861  Register result = temps.AcquireX();
862  if (offset_reg == no_reg) {
863  __ Add(result, addr_reg, Operand(offset_imm));
864  } else {
865  __ Add(result, addr_reg, Operand(offset_reg));
866  if (offset_imm != 0) __ Add(result, result, Operand(offset_imm));
867  }
868  return result;
869 }
870 
871 enum class Binop { kAdd, kSub, kAnd, kOr, kXor, kExchange };
872 
873 inline void AtomicBinop(LiftoffAssembler* lasm, Register dst_addr,
874  Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
875  LiftoffRegister value, LiftoffRegister result,
876  StoreType type, Binop op) {
877  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr, value, result};
878  if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg);
879  Register store_result = pinned.set(__ GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
880 
881  // {LiftoffCompiler::AtomicBinop} ensures that {result} is unique.
882  DCHECK(result.gp() != value.gp() && result.gp() != dst_addr &&
883  result.gp() != offset_reg);
884 
885  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
886  Register actual_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
887  lasm, temps, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
888 
889  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LSE)) {
890  CpuFeatureScope scope(lasm, LSE);
891  switch (op) {
892  case Binop::kAnd:
893  switch (type.value()) {
894  case StoreType::kI64Store8:
895  case StoreType::kI32Store8: {
896  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
897  Register temp = temps.AcquireW();
898  __ mvn(temp, value.gp().W());
899  __ ldclralb(temp, result.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
900  break;
901  }
902  case StoreType::kI64Store16:
903  case StoreType::kI32Store16: {
904  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
905  Register temp = temps.AcquireW();
906  __ mvn(temp, value.gp().W());
907  __ ldclralh(temp, result.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
908  break;
909  }
910  case StoreType::kI64Store32:
911  case StoreType::kI32Store: {
912  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
913  Register temp = temps.AcquireW();
914  __ mvn(temp, value.gp().W());
915  __ ldclral(temp, result.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
916  break;
917  }
918  case StoreType::kI64Store: {
919  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
920  Register temp = temps.AcquireX();
921  __ mvn(temp, value.gp());
922  __ ldclral(temp, result.gp(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
923  break;
924  }
925  default:
926  UNREACHABLE();
927  }
928  break;
929  case Binop::kSub:
930  switch (type.value()) {
931  case StoreType::kI64Store8:
932  case StoreType::kI32Store8: {
933  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
934  Register temp = temps.AcquireW();
935  __ neg(temp, value.gp().W());
936  __ ldaddalb(temp, result.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
937  break;
938  }
939  case StoreType::kI64Store16:
940  case StoreType::kI32Store16: {
941  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
942  Register temp = temps.AcquireW();
943  __ neg(temp, value.gp().W());
944  __ ldaddalh(temp, result.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
945  break;
946  }
947  case StoreType::kI64Store32:
948  case StoreType::kI32Store: {
949  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
950  Register temp = temps.AcquireW();
951  __ neg(temp, value.gp().W());
952  __ ldaddal(temp, result.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
953  break;
954  }
955  case StoreType::kI64Store: {
956  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(lasm);
957  Register temp = temps.AcquireX();
958  __ neg(temp, value.gp());
959  __ ldaddal(temp, result.gp(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
960  break;
961  }
962  default:
963  UNREACHABLE();
964  }
965  break;
966 #define ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(op, instr) \
967  case Binop::op: \
968  switch (type.value()) { \
969  case StoreType::kI64Store8: \
970  case StoreType::kI32Store8: \
971  __ instr##b(value.gp().W(), result.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr)); \
972  break; \
973  case StoreType::kI64Store16: \
974  case StoreType::kI32Store16: \
975  __ instr##h(value.gp().W(), result.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr)); \
976  break; \
977  case StoreType::kI64Store32: \
978  case StoreType::kI32Store: \
979  __ instr(value.gp().W(), result.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr)); \
980  break; \
981  case StoreType::kI64Store: \
982  __ instr(value.gp(), result.gp(), MemOperand(actual_addr)); \
983  break; \
984  default: \
985  UNREACHABLE(); \
986  } \
987  break;
988  ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(kAdd, ldaddal)
989  ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(kOr, ldsetal)
990  ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(kXor, ldeoral)
991  ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(kExchange, swpal)
992 #undef ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE
993  }
994  } else {
995  // Allocate an additional {temp} register to hold the result that should be
996  // stored to memory. Note that {temp} and {store_result} are not allowed to
997  // be the same register.
998  Register temp = temps.AcquireX();
999 
1000  Label retry;
1001  __ Bind(&retry);
1002  switch (type.value()) {
1003  case StoreType::kI64Store8:
1004  case StoreType::kI32Store8:
1005  __ ldaxrb(result.gp().W(), actual_addr);
1006  break;
1007  case StoreType::kI64Store16:
1008  case StoreType::kI32Store16:
1009  __ ldaxrh(result.gp().W(), actual_addr);
1010  break;
1011  case StoreType::kI64Store32:
1012  case StoreType::kI32Store:
1013  __ ldaxr(result.gp().W(), actual_addr);
1014  break;
1015  case StoreType::kI64Store:
1016  __ ldaxr(result.gp().X(), actual_addr);
1017  break;
1018  default:
1019  UNREACHABLE();
1020  }
1021 
1022  switch (op) {
1023  case Binop::kAdd:
1024  __ add(temp, result.gp(), value.gp());
1025  break;
1026  case Binop::kSub:
1027  __ sub(temp, result.gp(), value.gp());
1028  break;
1029  case Binop::kAnd:
1030  __ and_(temp, result.gp(), value.gp());
1031  break;
1032  case Binop::kOr:
1033  __ orr(temp, result.gp(), value.gp());
1034  break;
1035  case Binop::kXor:
1036  __ eor(temp, result.gp(), value.gp());
1037  break;
1038  case Binop::kExchange:
1039  __ mov(temp, value.gp());
1040  break;
1041  }
1042 
1043  switch (type.value()) {
1044  case StoreType::kI64Store8:
1045  case StoreType::kI32Store8:
1046  __ stlxrb(store_result.W(), temp.W(), actual_addr);
1047  break;
1048  case StoreType::kI64Store16:
1049  case StoreType::kI32Store16:
1050  __ stlxrh(store_result.W(), temp.W(), actual_addr);
1051  break;
1052  case StoreType::kI64Store32:
1053  case StoreType::kI32Store:
1054  __ stlxr(store_result.W(), temp.W(), actual_addr);
1055  break;
1056  case StoreType::kI64Store:
1057  __ stlxr(store_result.W(), temp.X(), actual_addr);
1058  break;
1059  default:
1060  UNREACHABLE();
1061  }
1062 
1063  __ Cbnz(store_result.W(), &retry);
1064  }
1065 }
1066 
1067 #undef __
1068 } // namespace liftoff

1070 void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicLoad(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
1071  Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
1072  LoadType type, LiftoffRegList /* pinned */,
1073  bool /* i64_offset */) {
1074  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1075  Register src_reg = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(this, temps, src_addr,
1076  offset_reg, offset_imm);
1077  switch (type.value()) {
1078  case LoadType::kI32Load8U:
1079  case LoadType::kI64Load8U:
1080  Ldarb(dst.gp().W(), src_reg);
1081  return;
1082  case LoadType::kI32Load16U:
1083  case LoadType::kI64Load16U:
1084  Ldarh(dst.gp().W(), src_reg);
1085  return;
1086  case LoadType::kI32Load:
1087  case LoadType::kI64Load32U:
1088  Ldar(dst.gp().W(), src_reg);
1089  return;
1090  case LoadType::kI64Load:
1091  Ldar(dst.gp().X(), src_reg);
1092  return;
1093  case LoadType::kI32Load8S:
1094  Ldarb(dst.gp().W(), src_reg);
1095  sxtb(dst.gp().W(), dst.gp().W());
1096  return;
1097  case LoadType::kI32Load16S:
1098  Ldarh(dst.gp().W(), src_reg);
1099  sxth(dst.gp().W(), dst.gp().W());
1100  return;
1101  default:
1102  UNREACHABLE();
1103  }
1104 }

1154 void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicStoreTaggedPointer(
1155  Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg, int32_t offset_imm, Register src,
1156  LiftoffRegList pinned, AtomicMemoryOrder memory_order,
1157  uint32_t* protected_store_pc) {
1158  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1159  Register dst_reg = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(this, temps, dst_addr,
1160  offset_reg, offset_imm);
1161  if (protected_store_pc != nullptr) {
1162  *protected_store_pc = pc_offset();
1163  }
1164  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
1165  Stlr(src.W(), dst_reg);
1166  } else {
1167  Stlr(src, dst_reg);
1168  }
1169 
1170  if (v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) return;
1171  // The write barrier.
1172  Label exit;
1173  CheckPageFlag(dst_addr, MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask,
1174  kZero, &exit);
1175  JumpIfSmi(src, &exit);
1176  CheckPageFlag(src, MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask, eq, &exit);
1177  // TODO(mliedtke): It would be great to reuse this calculation from the
1178  // liftoff::CalculateActualAddress above.
1179  Operand offset_op = offset_reg.is_valid() ? Operand(offset_reg.W(), UXTW)
1180  : Operand(offset_imm);
1181  if (offset_reg.is_valid() && offset_imm) {
1182  Register effective_offset = temps.AcquireX();
1183  Add(effective_offset.W(), offset_reg.W(), offset_imm);
1184  offset_op = effective_offset;
1185  }
1186  CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(dst_addr, offset_op, SaveFPRegsMode::kSave,
1187  StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
1188  bind(&exit);
1189 }

1239 
1240 void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicExchangeTaggedPointer(
1241  Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
1242  LiftoffRegister value, LiftoffRegister result, LiftoffRegList pinned) {
1243  // Perform the atomic exchange.
1244  {
1245  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1246  Register actual_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
1247  this, temps, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
1248  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LSE)) {
1249  CpuFeatureScope scope(this, LSE);
1250  if constexpr (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
1251  swpal(value.gp().W(), result.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
1252  add(result.gp().X(), result.gp().X(), kPtrComprCageBaseRegister);
1253  } else {
1254  swpal(value.gp(), result.gp(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
1255  }
1256  } else {
1257  DCHECK_NE(value, result);
1258  Label retry;
1259  Bind(&retry);
1260  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1261  Register store_result = temps.AcquireW();
1262  if constexpr (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
1263  ldaxr(result.gp().W(), actual_addr);
1264  stlxr(store_result.W(), value.gp().W(), actual_addr);
1265  } else {
1266  ldaxr(result.gp().X(), actual_addr);
1267  stlxr(store_result.W(), value.gp().X(), actual_addr);
1268  }
1269  Cbnz(store_result.W(), &retry);
1270  if constexpr (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
1271  add(result.gp().X(), result.gp().X(), kPtrComprCageBaseRegister);
1272  }
1273  }
1274  }
1275 
1276  if (v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) return;
1277  // Emit the write barrier.
1278  Label exit;
1279  CheckPageFlag(dst_addr, MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask,
1280  kZero, &exit);
1281  JumpIfSmi(value.gp(), &exit);
1282  CheckPageFlag(value.gp(), MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask, eq,
1283  &exit);
1284  // TODO(mliedtke): It would be great to reuse this calculation from the
1285  // liftoff::CalculateActualAddress above.
1286  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1287  Operand offset_op = offset_reg.is_valid() ? Operand(offset_reg.W(), UXTW)
1288  : Operand(offset_imm);
1289  if (offset_reg.is_valid() && offset_imm) {
1290  Register effective_offset = temps.AcquireX();
1291  Add(effective_offset.W(), offset_reg.W(), offset_imm);
1292  offset_op = effective_offset;
1293  }
1294  CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(dst_addr, offset_op, SaveFPRegsMode::kSave,
1295  StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
1296  bind(&exit);
1297 }
1298 
1299 void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicCompareExchange(
1300  Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
1301  LiftoffRegister expected, LiftoffRegister new_value, LiftoffRegister result,
1302  StoreType type, bool /* i64_offset */) {
1303  LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr, expected, new_value};
1304  if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg);
1305 
1306  Register result_reg = result.gp();
1307  if (pinned.has(result)) {
1308  result_reg = GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
1309  }
1310 
1311  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1312 
1313  Register actual_addr = liftoff::CalculateActualAddress(
1314  this, temps, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm);
1315 
1316  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LSE)) {
1317  CpuFeatureScope scope(this, LSE);
1318  switch (type.value()) {
1319  case StoreType::kI64Store8:
1320  case StoreType::kI32Store8:
1321  if (result.gp() != expected.gp()) {
1322  mov(result.gp().W(), expected.gp().W());
1323  }
1324  casalb(result.gp().W(), new_value.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
1325  break;
1326  case StoreType::kI64Store16:
1327  case StoreType::kI32Store16:
1328  if (result.gp() != expected.gp()) {
1329  mov(result.gp().W(), expected.gp().W());
1330  }
1331  casalh(result.gp().W(), new_value.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
1332  break;
1333  case StoreType::kI64Store32:
1334  case StoreType::kI32Store:
1335  if (result.gp() != expected.gp()) {
1336  mov(result.gp().W(), expected.gp().W());
1337  }
1338  casal(result.gp().W(), new_value.gp().W(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
1339  break;
1340  case StoreType::kI64Store:
1341  if (result.gp() != expected.gp()) {
1342  mov(result.gp().X(), expected.gp().X());
1343  }
1344  casal(result.gp().X(), new_value.gp().X(), MemOperand(actual_addr));
1345  break;
1346  default:
1347  UNREACHABLE();
1348  }
1349  } else {
1350  Register store_result = temps.AcquireW();
1351 
1352  Label retry;
1353  Label done;
1354  Bind(&retry);
1355  switch (type.value()) {
1356  case StoreType::kI64Store8:
1357  case StoreType::kI32Store8:
1358  ldaxrb(result_reg.W(), actual_addr);
1359  Cmp(result.gp().W(), Operand(expected.gp().W(), UXTB));
1360  B(ne, &done);
1361  stlxrb(store_result.W(), new_value.gp().W(), actual_addr);
1362  break;
1363  case StoreType::kI64Store16:
1364  case StoreType::kI32Store16:
1365  ldaxrh(result_reg.W(), actual_addr);
1366  Cmp(result.gp().W(), Operand(expected.gp().W(), UXTH));
1367  B(ne, &done);
1368  stlxrh(store_result.W(), new_value.gp().W(), actual_addr);
1369  break;
1370  case StoreType::kI64Store32:
1371  case StoreType::kI32Store:
1372  ldaxr(result_reg.W(), actual_addr);
1373  Cmp(result.gp().W(), Operand(expected.gp().W(), UXTW));
1374  B(ne, &done);
1375  stlxr(store_result.W(), new_value.gp().W(), actual_addr);
1376  break;
1377  case StoreType::kI64Store:
1378  ldaxr(result_reg.X(), actual_addr);
1379  Cmp(result.gp().X(), Operand(expected.gp().X(), UXTX));
1380  B(ne, &done);
1381  stlxr(store_result.W(), new_value.gp().X(), actual_addr);
1382  break;
1383  default:
1384  UNREACHABLE();
1385  }
1386 
1387  Cbnz(store_result.W(), &retry);
1388  Bind(&done);
1389  }
1390 
1391  if (result_reg != result.gp()) {
1392  mov(result.gp(), result_reg);
1393  }
1394 }

1426 void LiftoffAssembler::Move(Register dst, Register src, ValueKind kind) {

1428  Mov(dst.W(), src.W());

1432  }
1433 }

1435 void LiftoffAssembler::Move(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister src,
1436  ValueKind kind) {
1437  if (kind == kF32) {
1438  Fmov(dst.S(), src.S());
1439  } else if (kind == kF64) {
1440  Fmov(dst.D(), src.D());
1441  } else {
1442  DCHECK_EQ(kS128, kind);
1443  Mov(dst.Q(), src.Q());
1444  }
1445 }

1453 void LiftoffAssembler::Spill(int offset, WasmValue value) {
1454  RecordUsedSpillOffset(offset);
1455  MemOperand dst = liftoff::GetStackSlot(offset);
1456  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1457  CPURegister src = CPURegister::no_reg();
1458  switch (value.type().kind()) {
1459  case kI32:
1460  if (value.to_i32() == 0) {
1461  src = wzr;
1462  } else {
1463  src = temps.AcquireW();
1464  Mov(src.W(), value.to_i32());
1465  }
1466  break;
1467  case kI64:
1468  if (value.to_i64() == 0) {
1469  src = xzr;
1470  } else {
1471  src = temps.AcquireX();
1472  Mov(src.X(), value.to_i64());
1473  }
1474  break;
1475  default:
1476  // We do not track f32 and f64 constants, hence they are unreachable.
1477  UNREACHABLE();
1478  }
1479  Str(src, dst);
1480 }

1491 void LiftoffAssembler::FillStackSlotsWithZero(int start, int size) {
1492  // Zero 'size' bytes *below* start, byte at offset 'start' is untouched.
1493  DCHECK_LE(0, start);
1494  DCHECK_LT(0, size);
1495  DCHECK_EQ(0, size % 4);
1496  RecordUsedSpillOffset(start + size);
1497 
1498  int max_stp_offset = -start - size;
1499  // We check IsImmLSUnscaled(-start-12) because str only allows for unscaled
1500  // 9-bit immediate offset [-256,256]. If start is large enough, which can
1501  // happen when a function has many params (>=32 i64), str cannot be encoded
1502  // properly. We can use Str, which will generate more instructions, so
1503  // fallback to the general case below.
1504  if (size <= 12 * kStackSlotSize &&
1505  IsImmLSPair(max_stp_offset, kXRegSizeLog2) &&
1506  IsImmLSUnscaled(-start - 12)) {
1507  // Special straight-line code for up to 12 slots. Generates one
1508  // instruction per two slots (<= 7 instructions total).
1509  static_assert(kStackSlotSize == kSystemPointerSize);
1510  uint32_t remainder = size;
1511  for (; remainder >= 2 * kStackSlotSize; remainder -= 2 * kStackSlotSize) {
1512  stp(xzr, xzr, liftoff::GetStackSlot(start + remainder));
1513  }
1514 
1515  DCHECK_GE(12, remainder);
1516  switch (remainder) {
1517  case 12:
1518  str(xzr, liftoff::GetStackSlot(start + remainder));
1519  str(wzr, liftoff::GetStackSlot(start + remainder - 8));
1520  break;
1521  case 8:
1522  str(xzr, liftoff::GetStackSlot(start + remainder));
1523  break;
1524  case 4:
1525  str(wzr, liftoff::GetStackSlot(start + remainder));
1526  break;
1527  case 0:
1528  break;
1529  default:
1530  UNREACHABLE();
1531  }
1532  } else {
1533  // General case for bigger counts (5-8 instructions).
1534  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1535  Register address_reg = temps.AcquireX();
1536  // This {Sub} might use another temp register if the offset is too large.
1537  Sub(address_reg, fp, start + size);
1538  Register count_reg = temps.AcquireX();
1539  Mov(count_reg, size / 4);
1540 
1541  Label loop;
1542  bind(&loop);
1543  sub(count_reg, count_reg, 1);
1544  str(wzr, MemOperand(address_reg, kSystemPointerSize / 2, PostIndex));
1545  cbnz(count_reg, &loop);
1546  }
1547 }

1860 void LiftoffAssembler::IncrementSmi(LiftoffRegister dst, int offset) {
1861  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1862  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
1863  DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
1864  Register scratch = temps.AcquireW();
1865  Ldr(scratch, MemOperand(dst.gp(), offset));
1866  Add(scratch, scratch, Operand(Smi::FromInt(1)));
1867  Str(scratch, MemOperand(dst.gp(), offset));
1868  } else {
1869  Register scratch = temps.AcquireX();
1870  SmiUntag(scratch, MemOperand(dst.gp(), offset));
1871  Add(scratch, scratch, Operand(1));
1872  SmiTag(scratch);
1873  Str(scratch, MemOperand(dst.gp(), offset));
1874  }
1875 }

1877 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_divs(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs,
1878  Label* trap_div_by_zero,
1879  Label* trap_div_unrepresentable) {
1880  Register dst_w = dst.W();
1881  Register lhs_w = lhs.W();
1882  Register rhs_w = rhs.W();
1883  bool can_use_dst = !dst_w.Aliases(lhs_w) && !dst_w.Aliases(rhs_w);
1884  if (can_use_dst) {
1885  // Do div early.
1886  Sdiv(dst_w, lhs_w, rhs_w);
1887  }
1888  // Check for division by zero.
1889  Cbz(rhs_w, trap_div_by_zero);
1890  // Check for kMinInt / -1. This is unrepresentable.
1891  Cmp(rhs_w, -1);
1892  Ccmp(lhs_w, 1, NoFlag, eq);
1893  B(trap_div_unrepresentable, vs);
1894  if (!can_use_dst) {
1895  // Do div.
1896  Sdiv(dst_w, lhs_w, rhs_w);
1897  }
1898 }
1899 
1900 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_divu(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs,
1901  Label* trap_div_by_zero) {
1902  // Check for division by zero.
1903  Cbz(rhs.W(), trap_div_by_zero);
1904  // Do div.
1905  Udiv(dst.W(), lhs.W(), rhs.W());
1906 }

1908 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_rems(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs,
1909  Label* trap_div_by_zero) {
1910  Register dst_w = dst.W();
1911  Register lhs_w = lhs.W();
1912  Register rhs_w = rhs.W();
1913  // Do early div.
1914  // No need to check kMinInt / -1 because the result is kMinInt and then
1915  // kMinInt * -1 -> kMinInt. In this case, the Msub result is therefore 0.
1916  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1917  Register scratch = temps.AcquireW();
1918  Sdiv(scratch, lhs_w, rhs_w);
1919  // Check for division by zero.
1920  Cbz(rhs_w, trap_div_by_zero);
1921  // Compute remainder.
1922  Msub(dst_w, scratch, rhs_w, lhs_w);
1923 }
1924

1926  Label* trap_div_by_zero) {
1927  Register dst_w = dst.W();
1928  Register lhs_w = lhs.W();
1929  Register rhs_w = rhs.W();
1930  // Do early div.
1931  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1932  Register scratch = temps.AcquireW();
1933  Udiv(scratch, lhs_w, rhs_w);
1934  // Check for division by zero.
1935  Cbz(rhs_w, trap_div_by_zero);
1936  // Compute remainder.

1938 }

2039 bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_type_conversion(WasmOpcode opcode,
2040  LiftoffRegister dst,
2041  LiftoffRegister src, Label* trap) {
2042  switch (opcode) {
2043  case kExprI32ConvertI64:
2044  Mov(dst.gp().W(), src.gp().W());
2045  return true;
2046  case kExprI32SConvertF32:
2047  Fcvtzs(dst.gp().W(), src.fp().S()); // f32 -> i32 round to zero.
2048  // Check underflow and NaN.
2049  Fcmp(src.fp().S(), static_cast<float>(INT32_MIN));
2050  // Check overflow.
2051  Ccmp(dst.gp().W(), -1, VFlag, ge);
2052  B(trap, vs);
2053  return true;
2054  case kExprI32UConvertF32:
2055  Fcvtzu(dst.gp().W(), src.fp().S()); // f32 -> i32 round to zero.
2056  // Check underflow and NaN.
2057  Fcmp(src.fp().S(), -1.0);
2058  // Check overflow.
2059  Ccmp(dst.gp().W(), -1, ZFlag, gt);
2060  B(trap, eq);
2061  return true;
2062  case kExprI32SConvertF64: {
2063  // INT32_MIN and INT32_MAX are valid results, we cannot test the result
2064  // to detect the overflows. We could have done two immediate floating
2065  // point comparisons but it would have generated two conditional branches.
2066  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2067  VRegister fp_ref = temps.AcquireD();
2068  VRegister fp_cmp = temps.AcquireD();
2069  Fcvtzs(dst.gp().W(), src.fp().D()); // f64 -> i32 round to zero.
2070  Frintz(fp_ref, src.fp().D()); // f64 -> f64 round to zero.
2071  Scvtf(fp_cmp, dst.gp().W()); // i32 -> f64.
2072  // If comparison fails, we have an overflow or a NaN.
2073  Fcmp(fp_cmp, fp_ref);
2074  B(trap, ne);
2075  return true;
2076  }
2077  case kExprI32UConvertF64: {
2078  // INT32_MAX is a valid result, we cannot test the result to detect the
2079  // overflows. We could have done two immediate floating point comparisons
2080  // but it would have generated two conditional branches.
2081  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2082  VRegister fp_ref = temps.AcquireD();
2083  VRegister fp_cmp = temps.AcquireD();
2084  Fcvtzu(dst.gp().W(), src.fp().D()); // f64 -> i32 round to zero.
2085  Frintz(fp_ref, src.fp().D()); // f64 -> f64 round to zero.
2086  Ucvtf(fp_cmp, dst.gp().W()); // i32 -> f64.
2087  // If comparison fails, we have an overflow or a NaN.
2088  Fcmp(fp_cmp, fp_ref);
2089  B(trap, ne);
2090  return true;
2091  }
2092  case kExprI32SConvertSatF32:
2093  Fcvtzs(dst.gp().W(), src.fp().S());
2094  return true;
2095  case kExprI32UConvertSatF32:
2096  Fcvtzu(dst.gp().W(), src.fp().S());
2097  return true;
2098  case kExprI32SConvertSatF64:
2099  Fcvtzs(dst.gp().W(), src.fp().D());
2100  return true;
2101  case kExprI32UConvertSatF64:
2102  Fcvtzu(dst.gp().W(), src.fp().D());
2103  return true;
2104  case kExprI64SConvertSatF32:
2105  Fcvtzs(dst.gp().X(), src.fp().S());
2106  return true;
2107  case kExprI64UConvertSatF32:
2108  Fcvtzu(dst.gp().X(), src.fp().S());
2109  return true;
2110  case kExprI64SConvertSatF64:
2111  Fcvtzs(dst.gp().X(), src.fp().D());
2112  return true;
2113  case kExprI64UConvertSatF64:
2114  Fcvtzu(dst.gp().X(), src.fp().D());
2115  return true;
2116  case kExprI32ReinterpretF32:
2117  Fmov(dst.gp().W(), src.fp().S());
2118  return true;
2119  case kExprI64SConvertI32:
2120  Sxtw(dst.gp().X(), src.gp().W());
2121  return true;
2122  case kExprI64SConvertF32:
2123  Fcvtzs(dst.gp().X(), src.fp().S()); // f32 -> i64 round to zero.
2124  // Check underflow and NaN.
2125  Fcmp(src.fp().S(), static_cast<float>(INT64_MIN));
2126  // Check overflow.
2127  Ccmp(dst.gp().X(), -1, VFlag, ge);
2128  B(trap, vs);
2129  return true;
2130  case kExprI64UConvertF32:
2131  Fcvtzu(dst.gp().X(), src.fp().S()); // f32 -> i64 round to zero.
2132  // Check underflow and NaN.
2133  Fcmp(src.fp().S(), -1.0);
2134  // Check overflow.
2135  Ccmp(dst.gp().X(), -1, ZFlag, gt);
2136  B(trap, eq);
2137  return true;
2138  case kExprI64SConvertF64:
2139  Fcvtzs(dst.gp().X(), src.fp().D()); // f64 -> i64 round to zero.
2140  // Check underflow and NaN.
2141  Fcmp(src.fp().D(), static_cast<float>(INT64_MIN));
2142  // Check overflow.
2143  Ccmp(dst.gp().X(), -1, VFlag, ge);
2144  B(trap, vs);
2145  return true;
2146  case kExprI64UConvertF64:
2147  Fcvtzu(dst.gp().X(), src.fp().D()); // f64 -> i64 round to zero.
2148  // Check underflow and NaN.
2149  Fcmp(src.fp().D(), -1.0);
2150  // Check overflow.
2151  Ccmp(dst.gp().X(), -1, ZFlag, gt);
2152  B(trap, eq);
2153  return true;
2154  case kExprI64UConvertI32:
2155  Mov(dst.gp().W(), src.gp().W());
2156  return true;
2157  case kExprI64ReinterpretF64:
2158  Fmov(dst.gp().X(), src.fp().D());
2159  return true;
2160  case kExprF32SConvertI32:
2161  Scvtf(dst.fp().S(), src.gp().W());
2162  return true;
2163  case kExprF32UConvertI32:
2164  Ucvtf(dst.fp().S(), src.gp().W());
2165  return true;
2166  case kExprF32SConvertI64:
2167  Scvtf(dst.fp().S(), src.gp().X());
2168  return true;
2169  case kExprF32UConvertI64:
2170  Ucvtf(dst.fp().S(), src.gp().X());
2171  return true;
2172  case kExprF32ConvertF64:
2173  Fcvt(dst.fp().S(), src.fp().D());
2174  return true;
2175  case kExprF32ReinterpretI32:
2176  Fmov(dst.fp().S(), src.gp().W());
2177  return true;
2178  case kExprF64SConvertI32:
2179  Scvtf(dst.fp().D(), src.gp().W());
2180  return true;
2181  case kExprF64UConvertI32:
2182  Ucvtf(dst.fp().D(), src.gp().W());
2183  return true;
2184  case kExprF64SConvertI64:
2185  Scvtf(dst.fp().D(), src.gp().X());
2186  return true;
2187  case kExprF64UConvertI64:
2188  Ucvtf(dst.fp().D(), src.gp().X());
2189  return true;
2190  case kExprF64ConvertF32:
2191  Fcvt(dst.fp().D(), src.fp().S());
2192  return true;
2193  case kExprF64ReinterpretI64:
2194  Fmov(dst.fp().D(), src.gp().X());
2195  return true;
2196  default:
2197  UNREACHABLE();
2198  }
2199 }

2228 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_cond_jump(Condition cond, Label* label,
2229  ValueKind kind, Register lhs,
2230  Register rhs,
2231  const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
2232  switch (kind) {
2233  case kI32:
2234  if (rhs.is_valid()) {
2235  Cmp(lhs.W(), rhs.W());
2236  } else {
2237  Cmp(lhs.W(), wzr);
2238  }
2239  break;
2240  case kRef:
2241  case kRefNull:
2242  DCHECK(rhs.is_valid());
2243  DCHECK(cond == kEqual || cond == kNotEqual);
2244 #if defined(V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS)
2245  Cmp(lhs.W(), rhs.W());
2246 #else
2247  Cmp(lhs.X(), rhs.X());
2248 #endif
2249  break;
2250  case kI64:
2251  if (rhs.is_valid()) {
2252  Cmp(lhs.X(), rhs.X());
2253  } else {
2254  Cmp(lhs.X(), xzr);
2255  }
2256  break;
2257  default:
2258  UNREACHABLE();
2259  }
2260  B(label, cond);
2261 }

2300 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_set_cond(Condition cond, Register dst,
2301  DoubleRegister lhs,
2302  DoubleRegister rhs) {
2303  Fcmp(lhs.S(), rhs.S());
2304  Cset(dst.W(), cond);
2305  if (cond != ne) {
2306  // If V flag set, at least one of the arguments was a Nan -> false.
2307  Csel(dst.W(), wzr, dst.W(), vs);
2308  }
2309 }

2311 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_set_cond(Condition cond, Register dst,
2312  DoubleRegister lhs,
2313  DoubleRegister rhs) {
2314  Fcmp(lhs.D(), rhs.D());
2315  Cset(dst.W(), cond);
2316  if (cond != ne) {
2317  // If V flag set, at least one of the arguments was a Nan -> false.
2318  Csel(dst.W(), wzr, dst.W(), vs);
2319  }
2320 }
2321 
2322 bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_select(LiftoffRegister dst, Register condition,
2323  LiftoffRegister true_value,
2324  LiftoffRegister false_value,
2325  ValueKind kind) {
2326  if (kind != kI32 && kind != kI64 && kind != kF32 && kind != kF64)
2327  return false;
2328 
2329  Cmp(condition.W(), wzr);
2330  switch (kind) {
2331  default:
2332  UNREACHABLE();
2333  case kI32:
2334  Csel(dst.gp().W(), true_value.gp().W(), false_value.gp().W(), ne);
2335  break;
2336  case kI64:
2337  Csel(dst.gp().X(), true_value.gp().X(), false_value.gp().X(), ne);
2338  break;
2339  case kF32:
2340  Fcsel(dst.fp().S(), true_value.fp().S(), false_value.fp().S(), ne);
2341  break;
2342  case kF64:
2343  Fcsel(dst.fp().D(), true_value.fp().D(), false_value.fp().D(), ne);
2344  break;
2345  }
2346  return true;
2347 }
2348 
2349 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_smi_check(Register obj, Label* target,
2350  SmiCheckMode mode,
2351  const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
2352  Label* smi_label = mode == kJumpOnSmi ? target : nullptr;
2353  Label* not_smi_label = mode == kJumpOnNotSmi ? target : nullptr;
2354  JumpIfSmi(obj, smi_label, not_smi_label);
2355 }
2356 
2357 void LiftoffAssembler::LoadTransform(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
2358  Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
2359  LoadType type,
2360  LoadTransformationKind transform,
2361  uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
2362  bool i64_offset) {
2363  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2364  MemOperand src_op =
2365  transform == LoadTransformationKind::kSplat
2366  ? MemOperand{liftoff::GetEffectiveAddress(this, &temps, src_addr,
2367  offset_reg, offset_imm)}
2368  : liftoff::GetMemOp(this, &temps, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm,
2369  i64_offset);
2370  *protected_load_pc = pc_offset();
2371  MachineType memtype = type.mem_type();
2372 
2373  if (transform == LoadTransformationKind::kExtend) {
2374  if (memtype == MachineType::Int8()) {
2375  Ldr(dst.fp().D(), src_op);
2376  Sxtl(dst.fp().V8H(), dst.fp().V8B());
2377  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint8()) {
2378  Ldr(dst.fp().D(), src_op);
2379  Uxtl(dst.fp().V8H(), dst.fp().V8B());
2380  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int16()) {
2381  Ldr(dst.fp().D(), src_op);
2382  Sxtl(dst.fp().V4S(), dst.fp().V4H());
2383  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint16()) {
2384  Ldr(dst.fp().D(), src_op);
2385  Uxtl(dst.fp().V4S(), dst.fp().V4H());
2386  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
2387  Ldr(dst.fp().D(), src_op);
2388  Sxtl(dst.fp().V2D(), dst.fp().V2S());
2389  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Uint32()) {
2390  Ldr(dst.fp().D(), src_op);
2391  Uxtl(dst.fp().V2D(), dst.fp().V2S());
2392  }
2393  } else if (transform == LoadTransformationKind::kZeroExtend) {
2394  if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
2395  Ldr(dst.fp().S(), src_op);
2396  } else {
2397  DCHECK_EQ(MachineType::Int64(), memtype);
2398  Ldr(dst.fp().D(), src_op);
2399  }
2400  } else {
2401  DCHECK_EQ(LoadTransformationKind::kSplat, transform);
2402  if (memtype == MachineType::Int8()) {
2403  ld1r(dst.fp().V16B(), src_op);
2404  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int16()) {
2405  ld1r(dst.fp().V8H(), src_op);
2406  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int32()) {
2407  ld1r(dst.fp().V4S(), src_op);
2408  } else if (memtype == MachineType::Int64()) {
2409  ld1r(dst.fp().V2D(), src_op);
2410  }
2411  }
2412 }
2413 
2414 void LiftoffAssembler::LoadLane(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister src,
2415  Register addr, Register offset_reg,
2416  uintptr_t offset_imm, LoadType type,
2417  uint8_t laneidx, uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
2418  bool i64_offset) {
2419  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2420  MemOperand src_op{liftoff::GetEffectiveAddress(this, &temps, addr, offset_reg,
2421  offset_imm, i64_offset)};
2422 
2423  MachineType mem_type = type.mem_type();
2424  if (dst != src) {
2425  Mov(dst.fp().Q(), src.fp().Q());
2426  }
2427 
2428  *protected_load_pc = pc_offset();
2429  if (mem_type == MachineType::Int8()) {
2430  ld1(dst.fp().B(), laneidx, src_op);
2431  } else if (mem_type == MachineType::Int16()) {
2432  ld1(dst.fp().H(), laneidx, src_op);
2433  } else if (mem_type == MachineType::Int32()) {
2434  ld1(dst.fp().S(), laneidx, src_op);
2435  } else if (mem_type == MachineType::Int64()) {
2436  ld1(dst.fp().D(), laneidx, src_op);
2437  } else {
2438  UNREACHABLE();
2439  }
2440 }
2441 
2442 void LiftoffAssembler::StoreLane(Register dst, Register offset,
2443  uintptr_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
2444  StoreType type, uint8_t lane,
2445  uint32_t* protected_store_pc,
2446  bool i64_offset) {
2447  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2448  MemOperand dst_op{liftoff::GetEffectiveAddress(this, &temps, dst, offset,
2449  offset_imm, i64_offset)};
2450  if (protected_store_pc) *protected_store_pc = pc_offset();
2451 
2452  MachineRepresentation rep = type.mem_rep();
2453  if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord8) {
2454  st1(src.fp().B(), lane, dst_op);
2455  } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord16) {
2456  st1(src.fp().H(), lane, dst_op);
2457  } else if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord32) {
2458  st1(src.fp().S(), lane, dst_op);
2459  } else {
2460  DCHECK_EQ(MachineRepresentation::kWord64, rep);
2461  st1(src.fp().D(), lane, dst_op);
2462  }
2463 }

2878 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64x2_mul(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
2879  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
2880  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2881  VRegister tmp1 = temps.AcquireV(kFormat2D);
2882  VRegister tmp2 = temps.AcquireV(kFormat2D);
2883 
2884  // Algorithm copied from code-generator-arm64.cc with minor modifications:
2885  // - 2 (max number of scratch registers in Liftoff) temporaries instead of 3
2886  // - 1 more Umull instruction to calculate | cg | ae |,
2887  // - so, we can no longer use Umlal in the last step, and use Add instead.
2888  // Refer to comments there for details.
2889  Xtn(tmp1.V2S(), lhs.fp().V2D());
2890  Xtn(tmp2.V2S(), rhs.fp().V2D());
2891  Umull(tmp1.V2D(), tmp1.V2S(), tmp2.V2S());
2892  Rev64(tmp2.V4S(), rhs.fp().V4S());
2893  Mul(tmp2.V4S(), tmp2.V4S(), lhs.fp().V4S());
2894  Addp(tmp2.V4S(), tmp2.V4S(), tmp2.V4S());
2895  Shll(dst.fp().V2D(), tmp2.V2S(), 32);
2896  Add(dst.fp().V2D(), dst.fp().V2D(), tmp1.V2D());
2897 }

3252 
3253 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i8x16_shuffle(LiftoffRegister dst,
3254  LiftoffRegister lhs,
3255  LiftoffRegister rhs,
3256  const uint8_t shuffle[16],
3257  bool is_swizzle) {
3258  VRegister src1 = lhs.fp();
3259  VRegister src2 = rhs.fp();
3260  VRegister temp = dst.fp();
3261  if (dst == lhs || dst == rhs) {
3262  // dst overlaps with lhs or rhs, so we need a temporary.
3263  temp = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{lhs, rhs}).fp();
3264  }
3265 
3266  UseScratchRegisterScope scope(this);
3267 
3268  if (src1 != src2 && !AreConsecutive(src1, src2)) {
3269  // Tbl needs consecutive registers, which our scratch registers are.
3270  src1 = scope.AcquireV(kFormat16B);
3271  src2 = scope.AcquireV(kFormat16B);
3272  DCHECK(AreConsecutive(src1, src2));
3273  Mov(src1.Q(), lhs.fp().Q());
3274  Mov(src2.Q(), rhs.fp().Q());
3275  }
3276 
3277  int64_t imms[2] = {0, 0};
3278  for (int i = 7; i >= 0; i--) {
3279  imms[0] = (imms[0] << 8) | (shuffle[i]);
3280  imms[1] = (imms[1] << 8) | (shuffle[i + 8]);
3281  }
3282  DCHECK_EQ(0, (imms[0] | imms[1]) &
3283  (lhs == rhs ? 0xF0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0 : 0xE0E0E0E0E0E0E0E0));
3284 
3285  Movi(temp.V16B(), imms[1], imms[0]);
3286 
3287  if (src1 == src2) {
3288  Tbl(dst.fp().V16B(), src1.V16B(), temp.V16B());
3289  } else {
3290  Tbl(dst.fp().V16B(), src1.V16B(), src2.V16B(), temp.V16B());
3291  }
3292 }

3668  LiftoffRegister lhs,
3669  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
3670  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3671  VRegister tmp = temps.AcquireV(kFormat8H);
3672  VRegister right = rhs.fp().V8H();
3673  if (dst == rhs) {
3674  Mov(tmp, right);
3675  right = tmp;
3676  }
3677  Sqxtn(dst.fp().V8B(), lhs.fp().V8H());
3678  Sqxtn2(dst.fp().V16B(), right);
3679 }

3884 #define EMIT_QFMOP(instr, format) \
3885  if (dst == src3) { \
3886  instr(dst.fp().V##format(), src1.fp().V##format(), src2.fp().V##format()); \
3887  } else if (dst != src1 && dst != src2) { \
3888  Mov(dst.fp().V##format(), src3.fp().V##format()); \
3889  instr(dst.fp().V##format(), src1.fp().V##format(), src2.fp().V##format()); \
3890  } else { \
3891  DCHECK(dst == src1 || dst == src2); \
3892  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this); \
3893  VRegister tmp = temps.AcquireV(kFormat##format); \
3894  Mov(tmp, src3.fp().V##format()); \
3895  instr(tmp, src1.fp().V##format(), src2.fp().V##format()); \
3896  Mov(dst.fp().V##format(), tmp); \
3897  }

4144 bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_f16x8_pmin(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
4145  LiftoffRegister rhs) {
4146  if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(FP16)) {
4147  return false;
4148  }
4149  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4150 
4151  VRegister tmp = dst.fp();
4152  if (dst == lhs || dst == rhs) {
4153  tmp = temps.AcquireV(kFormat8H);
4154  }
4155 
4156  Fcmgt(tmp.V8H(), lhs.fp().V8H(), rhs.fp().V8H());
4157  Bsl(tmp.V16B(), rhs.fp().V16B(), lhs.fp().V16B());
4158 
4159  if (dst == lhs || dst == rhs) {
4160  Mov(dst.fp().V8H(), tmp);
4161  }
4162  return true;
4163 }

4178  Bsl(tmp.V16B(), rhs.fp().V16B(), lhs.fp().V16B());
4179 
4180  if (dst == lhs || dst == rhs) {

4231 bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_f16x8_demote_f64x2_zero(LiftoffRegister dst,
4232  LiftoffRegister src) {
4233  if (!CpuFeatures::IsSupported(FP16)) {
4234  return false;
4235  }
4236  // There is no vector f64 -> f16 conversion instruction,
4237  // so convert them by component using scalar version.
4238  // Convert high double to a temp reg first, because dst and src
4239  // can overlap.
4240  Mov(fp_scratch.D(), src.fp().V2D(), 1);
4241  Fcvt(fp_scratch.H(), fp_scratch.D());
4242 
4243  Fcvt(dst.fp().H(), src.fp().D());
4244  Mov(dst.fp().V8H(), 1, fp_scratch.V8H(), 0);
4245  return true;
4246 }

4267 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_inc_i32_at(Address address) {
4268  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4269  Register counter_addr = temps.AcquireX();
4270  Register value = temps.AcquireW();
4271  Mov(counter_addr.X(), Immediate(static_cast<uint64_t>(address)));
4272  Ldr(value, MemOperand(counter_addr.X(), 0));
4273  Add(value, value, 1);
4274  Str(value, MemOperand(counter_addr.X(), 0));
4275 }

4277 void LiftoffAssembler::StackCheck(Label* ool_code) {
4278  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4279  Register limit_address = temps.AcquireX();
4280  LoadStackLimit(limit_address, StackLimitKind::kInterruptStackLimit);
4281  Cmp(sp, limit_address);
4282  B(ool_code, ls);
4283 }

4299 void LiftoffAssembler::RecordSpillsInSafepoint(
4300  SafepointTableBuilder::Safepoint& safepoint, LiftoffRegList all_spills,
4301  LiftoffRegList ref_spills, int spill_offset) {
4302  LiftoffRegList fp_spills = all_spills & kFpCacheRegList;
4303  int spill_space_size = fp_spills.GetNumRegsSet() * kSimd128Size;
4304  LiftoffRegList gp_spills = all_spills & kGpCacheRegList;
4305  bool needs_padding = (gp_spills.GetNumRegsSet() & 1) != 0;
4306  if (needs_padding) {
4307  spill_space_size += kSystemPointerSize;
4308  ++spill_offset;
4309  }
4310  while (!gp_spills.is_empty()) {
4311  LiftoffRegister reg = gp_spills.GetLastRegSet();
4312  if (ref_spills.has(reg)) {
4313  safepoint.DefineTaggedStackSlot(spill_offset);
4314  }
4315  gp_spills.clear(reg);
4316  ++spill_offset;
4317  spill_space_size += kSystemPointerSize;
4318  }
4319  // Record the number of additional spill slots.
4320  RecordOolSpillSpaceSize(spill_space_size);
4321 }
4322 
4323 void LiftoffAssembler::DropStackSlotsAndRet(uint32_t num_stack_slots) {
4324  DropSlots(num_stack_slots);
4325  Ret();
4326 }

4328 void LiftoffAssembler::CallCWithStackBuffer(
4329  const std::initializer_list<VarState> args, const LiftoffRegister* rets,
4330  ValueKind return_kind, ValueKind out_argument_kind, int stack_bytes,
4331  ExternalReference ext_ref) {
4332  // The stack pointer is required to be quadword aligned.
4333  int total_size = RoundUp(stack_bytes, kQuadWordSizeInBytes);
4334  // Reserve space in the stack.
4335  Claim(total_size, 1);
4336 
4337  int arg_offset = 0;
4338  for (const VarState& arg : args) {
4339  liftoff::StoreToMemory(this, MemOperand{sp, arg_offset}, arg);
4340  arg_offset += value_kind_size(arg.kind());
4341  }
4342  DCHECK_LE(arg_offset, stack_bytes);
4343 
4344  // Pass a pointer to the buffer with the arguments to the C function.
4345  Mov(x0, sp);
4346 
4347  // Now call the C function.
4348  constexpr int kNumCCallArgs = 1;
4349  CallCFunction(ext_ref, kNumCCallArgs);
4350 
4351  // Move return value to the right register.
4352  const LiftoffRegister* next_result_reg = rets;
4353  if (return_kind != kVoid) {
4354  constexpr Register kReturnReg = x0;
4355  if (kReturnReg != next_result_reg->gp()) {
4356  Move(*next_result_reg, LiftoffRegister(kReturnReg), return_kind);
4357  }
4358  ++next_result_reg;
4359  }
4360 
4361  // Load potential output value from the buffer on the stack.
4362  if (out_argument_kind != kVoid) {
4363  if (out_argument_kind == kI16) {
4364  Ldrh(next_result_reg->gp(), MemOperand(sp));
4365  } else {
4366  Peek(liftoff::GetRegFromType(*next_result_reg, out_argument_kind), 0);
4367  }
4368  }
4369 
4370  Drop(total_size, 1);
4371 }
4372 
4373 void LiftoffAssembler::CallC(const std::initializer_list<VarState> args_list,
4374  ExternalReference ext_ref) {
4375  const int num_args = static_cast<int>(args_list.size());
4376  const VarState* const args = args_list.begin();
4377 
4378  // Note: If we ever need more than eight arguments we would need to load the
4379  // stack arguments to registers (via LoadToRegister) in pairs of two, then use
4380  // Stp with MemOperand{sp, -2 * kSystemPointerSize, PreIndex} to push them to
4381  // the stack.
4382 
4383  // Execute the parallel register move for register parameters.
4384  DCHECK_GE(arraysize(kCArgRegs), num_args);
4385  ParallelMove parallel_move{this};
4386  for (int reg_arg = 0; reg_arg < num_args; ++reg_arg) {
4387  parallel_move.LoadIntoRegister(LiftoffRegister{kCArgRegs[reg_arg]},
4388  args[reg_arg]);
4389  }
4390  parallel_move.Execute();
4391 
4392  // Now call the C function.
4393  CallCFunction(ext_ref, num_args);
4394 }

4404 void LiftoffAssembler::CallIndirect(const ValueKindSig* sig,
4405  compiler::CallDescriptor* call_descriptor,
4406  Register target) {
4407  // For Arm64, we have more cache registers than wasm parameters. That means
4408  // that target will always be in a register.
4409  DCHECK(target.is_valid());
4410  CallWasmCodePointer(target, call_descriptor->signature_hash());
4411 }
4412 
4413 void LiftoffAssembler::TailCallIndirect(
4414  compiler::CallDescriptor* call_descriptor, Register target) {
4415  DCHECK(target.is_valid());
4416  // When control flow integrity is enabled, the target is a "bti c"
4417  // instruction, which enforces that the jump instruction is either a "blr", or
4418  // a "br" with x16 or x17 as its destination.
4419  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4420  temps.Exclude(x17);
4421  Mov(x17, target);
4422  CallWasmCodePointer(x17, call_descriptor->signature_hash(),
4423  CallJumpMode::kTailCall);
4424 }

4447 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_store_nonzero_if_nan(Register dst,
4448  DoubleRegister src,
4449  ValueKind kind) {
4450  Label not_nan;
4451  if (kind == kF32) {
4452  Fcmp(src.S(), src.S());
4453  B(eq, &not_nan); // x != x iff isnan(x)
4454  // If it's a NaN, it must be non-zero, so store that as the set value.
4455  Str(src.S(), MemOperand(dst));
4456  } else {
4457  DCHECK_EQ(kind, kF64);
4458  Fcmp(src.D(), src.D());
4459  B(eq, &not_nan); // x != x iff isnan(x)
4460  // Double-precision NaNs must be non-zero in the most-significant 32
4461  // bits, so store that.
4462  St1(src.V4S(), 1, MemOperand(dst));
4463  }
4464  Bind(&not_nan);
4465 }
4466 
4467 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_s128_store_nonzero_if_nan(Register dst,
4468  LiftoffRegister src,
4469  Register tmp_gp,
4470  LiftoffRegister tmp_s128,
4471  ValueKind lane_kind) {
4472  DoubleRegister tmp_fp = tmp_s128.fp();
4473  if (lane_kind == kF32) {
4474  Fmaxv(tmp_fp.S(), src.fp().V4S());
4475  } else {
4476  DCHECK_EQ(lane_kind, kF64);
4477  Fmaxp(tmp_fp.D(), src.fp().V2D());
4478  }
4479  emit_store_nonzero_if_nan(dst, tmp_fp, lane_kind);
4480 }
4481 
4482 void LiftoffAssembler::emit_store_nonzero(Register dst) {
4483  Str(dst, MemOperand(dst));
4484 }

4486 void LiftoffStackSlots::Construct(int param_slots) {
4487  DCHECK_LT(0, slots_.size());
4488  // The stack pointer is required to be quadword aligned.
4489  asm_->Claim(RoundUp(param_slots, 2));
4490  for (auto& slot : slots_) {
4491  int poke_offset = slot.dst_slot_ * kSystemPointerSize;
4492  switch (slot.src_.loc()) {
4493  case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kStack: {
4494  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(asm_);
4495  CPURegister scratch = liftoff::AcquireByType(&temps, slot.src_.kind());
4496  asm_->Ldr(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(slot.src_offset_));
4497  asm_->Poke(scratch, poke_offset);
4498  break;
4499  }
4500  case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kRegister:
4501  asm_->Poke(liftoff::GetRegFromType(slot.src_.reg(), slot.src_.kind()),
4502  poke_offset);
4503  break;
4504  case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kIntConst:
4505  DCHECK(slot.src_.kind() == kI32 || slot.src_.kind() == kI64);
4506  if (slot.src_.i32_const() == 0) {
4507  Register zero_reg = slot.src_.kind() == kI32 ? wzr : xzr;
4508  asm_->Poke(zero_reg, poke_offset);
4509  } else {
4510  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(asm_);
4511  Register scratch =
4512  slot.src_.kind() == kI32 ? temps.AcquireW() : temps.AcquireX();
4513  asm_->Mov(scratch, int64_t{slot.src_.i32_const()});
4514  asm_->Poke(scratch, poke_offset);
4515  }
4516  break;
4517  }
4518  }
4519 }
